%I A396704 #7 Jun 28 2026 16:18:50
%S A396704 1,2,3,4,6,8,11
%N A396704 Maximum size of a B_3 set in {0,1}^n, where vectors are added componentwise over the integers.
%C A396704 Define addition on {0,1}^n componentwise as ordinary integer addition (not modulo 2), so a sum of three vectors lies in {0,1,2,3}^n. A subset S of {0,1}^n is a B_3 set iff all sums a+b+c with a, b, c in S (not necessarily distinct) are distinct as vectors; equivalently, the only solutions to a+b+c = d+e+f with a, b, c, d, e, f in S are those for which the multisets {a,b,c} and {d,e,f} are equal.
%C A396704 This is the B_3 analog of A309370, which is the B_2 (Sidon) case.
%C A396704 Every B_3 set is also a B_2 set, hence a(n) <= A309370(n).
%C A396704 Terms a(0)..a(6) were proven optimal by an exhaustive integer-program search (using the hyperoctahedral symmetry of {0,1}^n), and each maximum set was independently re-verified to be a B_3 set.
%C A396704 a(7) >= 16 and a(8) >= 19 (from computer search by iterated local search; not proven optimal).
%H A396704 William Blair, <a href="https://github.com/willblair0708/verified-combinatorics/tree/main/b3-binary">Maximum binary B_3 sets (n=0..6) and search program</a>
%F A396704 a(n) <= A309370(n), since every B_3 set is a B_2 set.
%e A396704 For n = 2 the vectors of {0,1}^2 are 00, 01, 10, 11. The set {00, 01, 10} is a B_3 set of size 3 (all sums of three of its elements are distinct). The full set {00, 01, 10, 11} is not a B_3 set, because 00 + 11 + 11 = 01 + 10 + 11 = (2,2) while {00,11,11} and {01,10,11} are different multisets. Hence a(2) = 3.
%o A396704 (Python)
%o A396704 from itertools import combinations_with_replacement as cwr
%o A396704 def is_B3(S, n):
%o A396704     sums = set()
%o A396704     for a, b, c in cwr(S, 3):
%o A396704         t = tuple(a[i] + b[i] + c[i] for i in range(n))
%o A396704         if t in sums:
%o A396704             return False
%o A396704         sums.add(t)
%o A396704     return True
%o A396704 # a(n) is the maximum size of a B_3 subset of {0,1}^n; is_B3 verifies a candidate set.
%Y A396704 Cf. A309370 (B_2 / Sidon analog), A385931 (B_3 sets of integers, distinct-element version), A002858 (Ulam numbers; first seven terms coincide but the sequences diverge at the next term).
%K A396704 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A396704 0,2
%A A396704 _William Blair_, Jun 02 2026
